comments: Vucevic (ORL) briefly grasps and immediately releases Gibson's (NYK) jersey shorts and the contact is marginal as it does not affect his ability to tip the rebound.
At the start of the drive, Barrett (NYK) places a resting arm to Fournier's (ORL) front and the contact does not affect his SQBR.
Gibson (NYK) moves laterally into Fournier's (ORL) path and marginal contact occurs during his driving shot attempt.
Birch (ORL) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact from Randle (NYK) in the post. Birch avoids making any contact to Randle's arm on his steal attempts.
Randle (NYK) and Birch (ORL) engage and disengage off ball in the post and the contact is marginal.
During the rebound, Birch (ORL) and Gibson (NYK) both make clean ball contact as they pursue the loose ball.
Prior to the block, Gibson (NYK) makes contact with Gordon's (ORL) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Birch (ORL) and Randle (NYK) engage and disengage off ball in the post and the contact is marginal.
Birch (ORL) maintains a legal guarding position on Randle (NYK) during the drive.
During the rebound, Vucevic (ORL) has a legal hand on Gibson's (NYK) body that gets caught in his jersey and he does not grab or pull it.
Gordon (ORL) grabs and pulls Randle's (NYK) jersey away from his body and the contact affects his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Fournier (ORL) makes contact with Burks' (NYK) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
During the rebound, Randle (NYK) makes clean hand on ball contact as he tries to dislodge the ball from Vucevic (ORL).
Burks (NYK) moves behind Fournier (ORL) and marginal contact occurs when Fournier leans forward and extends his legs backwards.
Vucevic (ORL) maintains a legal guarding position on Bullock (NYK) in the post and makes clean ball contact to temporarily dislodge it.
During the inbound, Fournier (ORL) and Ntilikina (NYK) engage and disengage off ball and the contact is marginal.
Fournier (ORL) extends his arm into Bullock's (NYK) path and marginal arm contact occurs that does not affect Bullock's ability to maintain control of the ball.
Fournier (ORL) makes clean contact when he gets his hands on the ball and a held ball is correctly whistled. Any arm contact with Bullock (NYK) prior to the contact with the ball is marginal.
Bullock (NYK) and Fournier (ORL) mutually engage as they approach the pick and any arm contact is deemed marginal as they are able to quickly disengage.
Vucevic (ORL) is slightly late to establish himself in Bullock's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs that does not affect Bullock's ability to maintain his legal guarding position.

Bullock (NYK) maintains a legal guarding position on Fournier (ORL) and makes clean ball contact to deflect the pass away. Any contact with Fournier as they both pursue the loose ball is deemed incidental.
Vucevic (ORL) is not able to get two hands on Burks (NYK) during his attempted take foul.
